The Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Kenya has announced the death of Amb. Wilfred Machage, High Commissioner of Kenya to Nigeria. According to a statement on the Ministry’s website, Machage collapsed at his Abuja residence on Saturday and was rushed to the hospital, where he passed on at 12.30 p.m. “Machage was appointed High Commissioner of Kenya to Nigeria by President Uhuru Kenyatta in January 2018 and accredited to 12 other countries within Central and Western Africa.   Liberia Telecoms firm, LoneStar Cell MTN, sues rival over…     Libyan PM survives assassination attempt     Cameroon refugee gives birth to triplets after narrow escape…   “He collapsed at home and was pronounced dead at the hospital after this unfortunate incident. - Advertisement - “The country has lost a dedicated compatriot,” the ministry said in the statement. (NAN) SPONSORED